text: I'm Papa I am a software development
engineer with the ec2 core platform and
I've been in AWS for about seven and a
half years now so my team is the
paperwork service team we are the
orchestration engine behind the entire
ec2 control thing the paperwork team is
one of the most diverse teams I've
worked on we have people from all
genders races in terms of diversity and
it makes it a really fun environment
because it makes
building ideas and bouncing ideas around
really safe and fun and it means that we
come out with the best solution every
time
so the Affinity groups are a really
amazing part of the AWS and broader
Amazon culture if you're part of the
Amazon Women in engineering affinity
group you can find a group of ladies who
might not be in the same team as you but
you know some of the best relationships
have come out of that affinity group
because you can find a mentor who's been
through the same things as you
career growth at AWS is very self-driven
your manager and your mentorship group
are going to support you but they're not
going to give you a career growth plan
on a plate
once you know what it is that you need
to do you go and do it
and nobody's going to do it for you but
you have the control to say within this
particular team I don't see the projects
that are going to stretch me shifting
between teams in order to find the
interesting work or the work that
excites you is part of what we expect
from Engineers we don't want people to
stagnate we want them to flow around
move ideas around and grow in that way
